import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='miles', bins=10, kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['miles'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2)
    plt.legend(['Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['miles'].median())])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of miles driven?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Miles Driven')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='gas', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('How has the average gas consumption changed over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Average Gas Consumption')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Gas Consumption'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

    plt.legend()
